    <note type="biography">
        <p>Swiss advocate. Studied in Marburg, Vienna, and Berlin, 1841–5. Doctor of law, Marburg, 1847. Professor extraordinarus of Roman law and commercial law, University of Zurich, 1851; professor, 1864–95. Sought to apply Darwinian principles to legal theory.</p></note>
